# NAME
#        allowlist — hosts the o3s egress firewall permits
#
# SYNOPSIS
#        address port...
#
# DESCRIPTION
#        Each non-empty line is one rule granting outbound TCP access to address
#        on the listed port(s). The gateway default-denies everything else. A '#'
#        begins a comment; blank lines are ignored.
#
#        The operands are:
#
#        address
#               A domain (subdomains are covered automatically), an IPv4 host,
#               or an IPv4 CIDR block.
#
#        port...
#               One or more TCP ports, separated by spaces. At least one port is
#               required; there is no default.
#
# EXAMPLES
#        github.com  443 22
#               Permit HTTPS and SSH to github.com.
#
#        pypi.org  443
#               Permit HTTPS to pypi.org.
#
#        10.8.0.0/24  443
#               Permit HTTPS to every host in the 10.8.0.0/24 subnet.
#
# FILES
#        Edits take effect after: docker restart o3s-gateway

